reviews.review_text: AN HONOR TO BE THE FIRST TO REVIEW THIS I have been very impressed with the amazing quality of the recordings made by Jim Vita (R.I.P.)  That being said, I have always felt very blessed to have attended these 2 nights in Hartford.  They were both epic performances, IMHO!  The band comes right out of the shoot (Just like Hampton 5-1-81, which I also attended) with a blistering version of ALABAMA GETAWAY.  The whole first set just kicks butt.  Of course, as has been noted by so many, the 2nd set is legendary with an absolutely mind-blowing SCARLET > FIRE.  I remember being totally in awe when I saw this stellar performance.  The peak the Jerry hits on the 2nd solo in FIRE just floored me.  What a show!
